main event: A number of unidentified objects were observed near Edwards AFB in California on November 5, 1954.
interesting points: The objects were described as blinking and brighter than stars.
The objects moved in an irregular course.
The investigation concluded that the objects were likely aircraft, but there was insufficient data to make a definitive evaluation.
The report indicates that the objects were initially thought to be spacecraft, but were later determined to be something else, possibly aircraft.
